O God! Thou art my God alone;  
In midnight’s hush, I seek Thy face;  
No star nor moon can make Thee known,  
Yet in my heart, Thou leav’st Thy trace.  
When I am lost, when tempest tossed,  
Thy whisper calms the rolling sea;  
To Thee my every hope is cast—  
Thy love, my one eternity.  
Through wilderness and weary days,  
My soul shall cling, unmoved, to Thee;  
O God! Thou art my God always,  
My refuge through infinity.

Please spare me your secrets, I’m fragile with truth;
My heart is a lantern, too thin for your proof.
Let the unsaid remain where the shadows reside—
I’ll cherish the peace that no riddles divide.
Let’s walk in the sunlight, unfettered and free;
Your secrets are yours, not meant for me.
